# Vercel-specific ignore at the repo root.
#
# The web build is the only thing Vercel needs to see from this repo.
# Everything Electron-related is huge and useless on Vercel:
#   • dist/   ~3 GB of every Electron installer ever built
#   • node_modules/   500 MB of Electron toolchain
#   • assets/, main.js, preload.js   Electron-only runtime files
#
# Vercel CLI does NOT reliably respect .gitignore for monorepo deploys
# (verified by a 3 GB upload + Internal Server Error before this file
# existed). Mirror the relevant gitignore exclusions here.

# Heavy excluded by .gitignore — re-exclude here for Vercel
node_modules
dist
out
dist2
.git
.github
.claude
.vercel
*.log
.env
.env.local

# Electron-only runtime files Vercel doesn't execute
# (package.json + package-lock.json are kept — Vercel reads them for
# project metadata even though our installCommand cd's into web/)
main.js
preload.js
assets
PM_Roadmapper_User_Guide.md
ROADMAP_OS_USER_GUIDE.md
README.md
public

# Supabase — deployed separately via supabase CLI / MCP
supabase

# Web build artifacts — Vercel builds fresh
web/node_modules
web/public
web/.vercel

# Editor / OS clutter
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
